# module: eng.case
# status: supported-case-manifest-artifact-seed; planned native runner
# purpose: per-case manifests for sample-to-run workflows.
#
# Current implementation:
#   Promoted sample tables with case_id columns produce
#   typed_payload.case_manifests[] entries with case_id, sample row number,
#   source row, deterministic sample row hash, and duplicate/missing case_id
#   status. Runtime result materialization also links process expected outputs
#   whose path contains a case_id segment. When an expected output is a
#   case_manifest.json file, EngLang reads it and enriches the native case
#   manifest with case_dir, generated_input_file, process_statuses,
#   output_artifacts, result_files, metrics, and failure_reason.
#
# Native apply/run/collect syntax, cache/resume status, and automatic case
# directory execution remain planned. Workflow examples still expand fixture
# cases explicitly while exposing the same reviewable CaseManifest contract.
#
# Current CaseManifest fields:
#   case_id
#   sample row hash
#   case directory
#   generated input file
#   process bindings
#   process command and status records
#   output artifacts
#   result files
#   metrics
#   failure reason
#
# Planned extensions:
#   native case runner
#   cache/resume status
#
# Non-goal:
#   loops that mutate files without a case manifest should not become the
#   preferred batch-workflow pattern.
